        public CompletableFuture open()
                       throws ChannelLifetimeException
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        Perform required open procedures. For example, in NDN this may involve registering prefixes and event handlers. Note that the corresponding close() method is inherited from AutoCloseable.

        This method must be protected using the ChannelPermission's open action.

        Returns:
        a future that completes once the channel is open and ready for use
        Throws:
        ChannelLifetimeException - if the channel fails to open

      • publish

        public void publish(Message message)
             throws ChannelIOException
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        Publish a message on this channel. Messages must be available on the network for the persistence period specified during channel construction. Note that this operation may not "send" any network traffic; in pull-based paradigms such as NDN the subscribers may be responsible for requesting published messages.

        This method must be protected using the ChannelPermission's publish action.

        Parameters:
        message - the Message to publish on this channel
        Throws:
        ChannelIOException - when the channel fails to publish Messages

      • isPublishing

        public boolean isPublishing()
        Returns:
        true when the Channel has published at least one message; false otherwise

      • subscribe

        public void subscribe(OnPublish callback)
               throws ChannelIOException
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        Subscribe to messages on this channel. Channel implementations should allow multiple calls to this method that return published messages to all registered callbacks. Users should quickly exit the callback to avoid taxing the thread pool.

        This method must be protected using the ChannelPermission's subscribe action.

        Parameters:
        callback - the OnPublish code to run when a message is received
        Throws:
        ChannelIOException - when the channel subscribe operation fails

      • isSubscribing

        public boolean isSubscribing()
        Returns:
        true when the Channel is successfully subscribed to receive messages; false otherwise

      • latest

        public CompletableFuture latest()
                         throws ChannelIOException
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        Retrieve the latest message available on this channel. Note that channel messages expire so no message may be available when the user calls this method.

        This method must be protected using the ChannelPermission's subscribe action; this uses the same action as Channel.subscribe(OnPublish) since they both "retrieve messages"

        Returns:
        the latest Message published on this channel
        Throws:
        ChannelIOException - when the channel fails to retrieve the latest Message
